"""
        choose values that simplify the calculations and are similar to
        observed values
    """
Y = firm.get_Y(K, L, p, method)
assert np.allclose(Y, expected, atol=1e-06)
pytest.mark.parametrize('K,L,p,method,expected', [(K1, L1, p1, 'SS',
    expected1), (K1, L1, p2, 'SS', expected2), (K3, L3, p3, 'SS', expected3
    ), (K4, L4, p4, 'TPI', expected4), (K4, L4, p5, 'TPI', expected5)], ids
    =['epsilon=1.0,SS', 'epsilon=0.2,SS', 'epsilon=1.2,SS',
    'epsilon=1.0,TP', 'epsilon=1.0,TP,varyZ'])
